## What still needs to be done

### P0 — Blocking production stability

#### 1. MinIO topology workflow must create data dirs and buckets
The topology workflow renders configs and restarts MinIO, but does NOT:
  - Create the data subdirectory on each node's mount point
  - Create the MinIO buckets (globular, globular-config) after pool formation
Without these, MinIO reports "drive not found" and the repository can't
serve packages. Currently requires manual `mkdir` and `mc mb`.

Fix: the topology workflow's post-apply step should:
  - SSH to each node and create <mount>/<data-subdir> with globular ownership
  - After all nodes are healthy, create buckets via mc or MinIO API
  - Verify bucket accessibility before marking topology converged

#### 2. Node-agent ScyllaDB post-install must configure scylla.yaml
The infrastructure installer for ScyllaDB installs apt packages but does
NOT configure scylla.yaml. Without seeds, cluster_name, dev mode, and
io_properties, ScyllaDB starts with defaults and fails to join Raft.

Fix: node-agent post-install for scylladb must:
  - Set listen_address/rpc_address to node's routable IP
  - Set seeds from etcd or controller
  - Set cluster_name to match cluster domain (globular.internal)
  - Set endpoint_snitch to SimpleSnitch
  - Enable developer_mode on small nodes (< 16GB RAM)
  - Write io_properties.yaml with reasonable defaults
  - Ensure data dirs exist with scylla ownership

#### 3. DNS reconciler must use public IP for external NS records
The DNS reconciler sets dns.<external-domain> A records to the node's
private IP (e.g. 10.0.0.9). For ACME DNS-01 to work, Let's Encrypt
must reach the DNS server from the internet, so the A record must be
the public IP (96.20.133.54).

Fix: when publishing dns.<zone> for external domains (publish_external=true),
use the discovered public IP instead of the node's internal IP.

#### 4. DNS zones must be loaded on all DNS instances after restart
DNS zones are in-memory. When a DNS service restarts, it loses external
zones (globular.io, globular.cloud). The DNS reconciler re-pushes records
but only to instances that already have the zone registered. New/restarted
instances get A records but not the zone registration.

Fix: the DNS reconciler should call SetDomains on every DNS instance,
not just the one the local provider happened to connect to. Or: persist
managed domain list in etcd and load on DNS service startup.

#### 5. etcd auto-rejoin too aggressive
The reconciler marks nodes RejoinRequired on transient etcd unavailability.
Needs cooldown/retry (N consecutive failures before triggering).

### P1 — AI knowledge plane (new)

#### 13. Awareness bundle not fetched or installed at day-0/day-1
The `BootstrapAwarenessReady` phase in the controller is wired but the node-agent
side is unimplemented: no code to fetch, extract, or report an `AWARENESS_BUNDLE`
artifact. No `AWARENESS_BUNDLE` artifact is published in the repository.

Consequences:
  - `/var/lib/globular/awareness/current/` never exists after day-0
  - ops-knowledge auto-seed (`seed_ops_knowledge` HealAuto) cannot fire
    because the bundle dir is missing → cluster-doctor emits
    `ops_knowledge.seed_deferred / bundle_dir_missing` → "manual seed required"
  - awareness-graph Oxigraph store starts empty; cluster-doctor only proposes
    (HealPropose) a restart — never auto-heals

Fix:
  a. Package the awareness bundle (ops-knowledge YAML + awareness.nt) as an
     AWARENESS_BUNDLE artifact in the release pipeline and publish it.
  b. Implement node-agent fetch + extract for AWARENESS_BUNDLE kind:
     download from repository, extract to /var/lib/globular/awareness/<build_id>/,
     write /var/lib/globular/awareness/current symlink, report build_id in
     InstalledBuildIDs["awareness_bundle"] so the controller advances the
     BootstrapAwarenessReady phase.
  c. After the bundle is in place, the cluster-doctor HealAuto for
     ops_knowledge.seed_deferred will fire automatically (no further changes).
  d. For awareness-graph: either change Disposition to HealAuto so the service
     is restarted automatically when the graph is empty after bundle install,
     or load the .nt directly via the loadnt path post-extract (avoids
     requiring a restart).

### P1 — Operational improvements

#### 6. MinIO topology workflow auto-retry
Topology workflow doesn't auto-retry on transient failure. Operator must
re-run `objectstore topology apply` manually. Controller should retry
when applied_generation < desired_generation and no workflow in-flight.

#### 7. Sequential ScyllaDB Raft join
Two simultaneous joins stall the second node's Raft. Auto-recovery handles
it (~10 min) but sequencing would be faster.

#### 8. VIP/ingress spec should survive cluster wipe
Keepalived VIP config is etcd-only. Consider persisting as a file alongside
etcd for re-seeding on recovery.

#### 9. clean-node.sh must flush iptables rules
Found iptables DROP rules blocking etcd ports from previous stale-node
mitigation. clean-node.sh should:
  - Flush all iptables rules referencing the node's IP on ports 2379/2380
  - Remove the node from any other cluster member's iptables
  - Also clean up on the bootstrap node (flush rules for the joining IP)

#### 10. Service registration uses UUIDs instead of canonical names
After fresh install, services register with UUID-based IDs instead of
canonical names. xDS can't route gRPC-Web by service name. The service
startup logic prefers UUID config files over named ones.

#### 11. Upstream source URL template seeded with typo
The Day-0 installer seeds /globular/repository/upstreams/globulario-github
with indexUrl containing {tag/release-index.json} instead of {tag}/release-index.json.
Fix the seed template in the installer code.

### P2 — Release pipeline

#### 12. BOM delta verification — VERIFIED
v1.1.7 sync: 4 imported, 52 skipped, 0 rejected. Delta detection works.
The source-based change detection correctly identified only the packages
whose Go source changed between releases.

